a:1:{s:7:"encoded";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:2307:"<h2>WP Edit Pro Version 4.1.1</h2>\r\n<h3>IMPORTANT SECURITY RELEASE &#8211; Please Update Immediately</h3>\r\n<p>I believe a security vulnerability has been found in WP Edit Pro.  Specifically; it pertains to the script used to upload custom fonts.  For this reason, I have temporarily removed the custom fonts option.</p>\r\n<p>I will replace this option with a more secure approach in the next plugin version.</p>\r\n<h4>Miscellaneous</h4>\r\n<p>Some other small tweaks in this version include:</p>\r\n<p>1) A license check was performed whenever the plugin options were saved.  This sometimes caused legitimately registered licenses to self-deactivate.  This particular license check has been removed from the plugin.</p>\r\n<p>2) The dropbox API key alert has been removed.</p>\r\n<p>3) The license extension url in the admin notice has been corrected.</p>\r\n<Img align="left" border="0" height="1" width="1" alt="" style="border:0;float:left;margin:0;padding:0;width:1px!important;height:1px!important;" hspace="0" src="http://feeds.feedblitz.com/~/i/119260477/0/wpeditpro">\r\n<div style="clear:both;padding-top:0.2em;"><a title="Like on Facebook" href="http://feeds.feedblitz.com/_/28/119260477/wpeditpro"><img height="20" src="http://assets.feedblitz.com/i/fblike20.png" style="border:0;margin:0;padding:0;"></a>&#160;<a title="Share on Google+" href="http://feeds.feedblitz.com/_/30/119260477/wpeditpro"><img height="20" src="http://assets.feedblitz.com/i/googleplus20.png" style="border:0;margin:0;padding:0;"></a>&#160;<a title="Pin it!" href="http://feeds.feedblitz.com/_/29/119260477/wpeditpro,"><img height="20" src="http://assets.feedblitz.com/i/pinterest20.png" style="border:0;margin:0;padding:0;"></a>&#160;<a title="Tweet This" href="http://feeds.feedblitz.com/_/24/119260477/wpeditpro"><img height="20" src="http://assets.feedblitz.com/i/twitter20.png" style="border:0;margin:0;padding:0;"></a>&#160;<a title="Subscribe by ema